name: Oregon's Big Country (copy)
description: Linking up the best of Oregon's Big Country with forgotten wagon roads and rugged overland travel. Cross three mountain ranges, a desert playa, visit five hot springs, and enjoy the solitude of vast empty landscapes.

points_of_interest.name: Willow Creek Hot Springs
points_of_interest.description: Photos show real water in the Willow Creek, so possible water source.  Prob necessary one?

points_of_interest.name: Alvord Hot Springs
points_of_interest.description: Very basic candy bars and soda in the Alvord Hot Springs office.

points_of_interest.name: Alvord Hot Springs
points_of_interest.description: Great rustic Hot Springs. Fee for soaking but free and after hours available if you pay for a campsite.

points_of_interest.name: Good Car Camping before/after the trip
Denio Junction Store, Restaurant, and Bar
points_of_interest.description: Hot food, cold drinks, small grocery selection.

points_of_interest.name: Bog Hot Spring
points_of_interest.description: Hot stream, many pools to choose from.

points_of_interest.name: Opal Mines
points_of_interest.description: May have some supplies? Only summer months. Call ahead.

points_of_interest.name: Pike Creek
points_of_interest.description: Water, hiking, camping (pay for sites at Alvord Hot Springs)

points_of_interest.name: Campground, not a lot of shelter
Virgin Valley Hot Springs
points_of_interest.description: Not very hot, but neat warm pond and continuously running indoor showers.

points_of_interest.name: Campsite
points_of_interest.description: Last shade tree for a while, good campsite. Reliable water in the creek.

points_of_interest.name: Store
points_of_interest.description: Decent small general store, not open winter months.

points_of_interest.name: Frenchglen Hotel
points_of_interest.description: Unique lodging and good warm meals.

points_of_interest.name: Hotel Diamond
points_of_interest.description: Amazing food and beer and small snack store.  Limited hours/season. Open till 2pm for lunch.  Dinner at 6:30, reservations only.

points_of_interest.name: Great campsite with water just up the road
Willow Creek
points_of_interest.description: Filter water from creek or beaver ponds just upstream from parking lot.

points_of_interest.name: Stream Crossing, probably dry in late summer
Small pond, may dry up in summer
Creek water probably reliable through summer
Good views
points_of_interest.description: Access to Funnel Canyon. (shortcut back to Frenchglen, NO WATER available until roaring springs)

points_of_interest.name: Seasonal Roads (non-motorized access is permitted)
points_of_interest.description: No motorized access through much of Hart Mountain until after June 15th, or August 15th on Barnhardy Rd
